::BEGIN:TRG1
talk:#corpus chat:brian The republic is home to the Kalmyks, a people of Mongol origin who are primarily of Buddhist faith.
::END:TRG1

::BEGIN:TRG2
talk:#corpus chat:brian Kalmykia is unique in that it has been the home in successive periods to many major world religions and ideologies.
::END:TRG2

::BEGIN:TRG3
talk:#corpus chat:brian The Kalmyks were subject to the policies of de-cossackization where villages were destroyed, temples/monasteries were burned down and executions were indiscriminate.
::END:TRG3

::BEGIN:TRG4
talk:#corpus chat:brian According to the Kurgan hypothesis, the upland regions of modern-day Kalmykia formed part of the cradle of Indo-European culture.
::END:TRG4

::BEGIN:TRG5
talk:#corpus chat:brian With the annexation of the territory by the Russian Empire, Christianity arrived with Slavic settlers, before all religion was suppressed after the Russian Revolution.
::END:TRG5
